\begin_layout Standard
Cell arrangements in a tissue can be categorized in a number of ways on
 the spectrum between healthy tissue to tumor formation:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Normal
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Hyperplasia - increase in the number of cells in the tissue while still
 appearing normal under a microscope.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Neoplasia - uncontrolled hyperplasia
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Dysplasia - cells begin to appear abnormal but are not yet cancer.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Cancer
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
An illustration can be found in figure 
