\begin_layout Subsubsection
The ABCDE of diagnosis 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Anapalesia - cells don't follow regular tissue organization.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Bizarre - cells are not uniform and irregular in shape and size, large cells
 are generally the cancerous ones.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Chromatin - extra chromatin, darker than usual cells.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Displasia - displaced growth.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Edges - well defined or messy edges.
 The messy edges point to cancer.
\end_layout

